snippet.title: Gaming with muscular dystrophy | Project GameFace featuring Lance Carr | Google
snippet.description:
Lance Carr - a Colorado gamer with a rare form of muscular dystrophy - was at home playing video games one afternoon when a fire turned his life upside down. 

This year at I/O, we’re celebrating Lance’s resilient return to gaming. Over the last year, Lance collaborated with a team of Googlers to co-create a new technology that uses MediaPipe and Tensor Flow Lite to turn facial gestures into mouse movements. The resulting solution is now open-sourced and available for everyone to game and create with. 

For a quick recap of Google I/O, check out this video: https://youtu.be/QpBTM0GO6xI

snippet.title: Developers guide to BigQuery export for Google Analytics 4
snippet.description:
With Google Analytics 4 (GA4), anyone can set up export of granular measurement data to BigQuery.

In this session, you will learn how to use the BigQuery export for solving business problems, doing complex reporting, implementing advanced use cases with ML models, and creating custom audiences by joining with first-party data. You can use this framework for detailed or large-scale data analysis. We will also share some best practices to get you started.

snippet.description:

But maybe you haven't added those amazing features you've been wanting as you don't have time to learn the deep learning concepts required to make a good ML solution. Fortunately, you now have MediaPipe which can create custom cross-platform ML solutions for common tasks without ML expertise. Learn how to create custom solutions and leave with exciting ideas to supercharge your web app.

snippet.title: Learning Sign Language with PopSign | Google
snippet.description:
Learning sign language can be challenging, especially for new parents of deaf children. This year at I/O, we’re sharing an exciting new project that will hopefully make it easier.

A group of students from the Georgia Institute of Technology and the Rochester Institute of Technology are working with Google engineers and the Kaggle community to make learning Sign Language more accessible, and more fun using AI. 

Learn more: http://sites.gatech.edu/popsign

For a quick recap of Google I/O, check out this video: https://youtu.be/QpBTM0GO6xI

snippet.title: Introducing our New Project Starline Prototype | Google
snippet.description:
In 2021, Google introduced Project Starline, a new technology project that uses breakthrough communication advancements to help people feel like they’re together — even when they’re hundreds of miles apart.

Today, we are excited to announce the latest version of our prototype - which is now smaller and more practical for everyday use thanks to advancements in AI/ML.

See it in action and hear directly from our partners at Salesforce and T-mobile  on how Project Starline is helping them build more personal connections through the distance.

For a quick recap of Google I/O, check out this video: https://youtu.be/QpBTM0GO6xI
